    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integrity algorithm selection in stream security container initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe `stream_security_container_init()` function was not correctly initializing integrity contexts due to incorrect enum values being used in the integrity algorithm selection logic. This caused unexpected behavior when establishing security contexts.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/SECU/secu_defs.c`: Fixed enum values in `stream_integrity_init()` and `stream_integrity_free()` functions to use EIA* values instead of EEA* values for integrity algorithms.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `stream_security_container_init()` with any integrity algorithm other than EEA0_ALG_ID, the function would either:\n1. Select the wrong integrity algorithm implementation\n2. Trigger an assertion failure due to unrecognized algorithm ID\n3. Fail to properly initialize the integrity context\n\nThis issue was particularly noticeable when using EIA1 or EIA2 algorithms where the wrong algorithm would be selected, leading to incorrect integrity protection of NAS messages.\n\nThe fix ensures that integrity algorithms are properly selected and initialized according to their correct enum values.\n"
}